cs.NI, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.CR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a scheme for transmission in wireless sensor networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The proposed scheme involves dividing the network into logical regions, which can be seen as a form of multiagent system. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The closed-loop feedback mechanism used in the proposed scheme can be seen as a control system. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses link quality estimation and compensation, which involves information theory concepts. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the main focus of the paper, the proposed scheme can have implications for security in wireless sensor networks.
